<br>
Now, I'll use an example of what happened and tell it like a story. There was one guy there who won a piece of armor. When more dropped that he wanted, he had his other guild friends who didn't need it enter their name. One of those guild people won and they say right away that they will let this guy who already won loot it.<br>
<br>
My question is, is that fair? That's in no way NBG and it seemed that guild's members that were there manipulated us. It was my belief at the time that most guilds don't even let non-guild people enter a lotto. Yet we did and gave quite a fair chance at loot for everyone, and still they manipulate us. I ask because I've always wondered.  <p><b> The SuperMonk!<BR>
